Feedback Report: Guide Improvements for Next Release

Based on the troubleshooting of the Hardware Acceleration (VA-API) integration and Appendix D, here are the required updates to ensure compatibility with Bazzite's security model:

1. Phase 10 Expansion: Enabling Hardware Acceleration (AMD/Intel)

The Problem: Enabling GPU passthrough triggers an internal AIO script that re-manages GIDs and folder ownership. This is blocked by the Immutable Guard and SELinux by default.

The Fix:

Add NEXTCLOUD_ENABLE_DRI_DEVICE=true to the environment section of the Mastercontainer.

Add /dev/dri:/dev/dri to the devices section.

Mandatory Warning: Users must run sudo chattr -i /srv/nextcloud-data before starting containers for the first time after this change to allow the container to initialize ownership, then re-apply sudo chattr +i once the containers are Green.

2. Appendix D: Watchtower Compose Correction

The Problem: The current Watchtower snippet is missing the network definition, causing it to fail to start because it cannot find the nextcloud-aio network.

The Fix: Update the Compose file to include:

code
Yaml
download
content_copy
expand_less
networks:
  nextcloud-aio:
    external: true

And add the networks: block to the watchtower service definition.

3. Critical Security Clarification (Phase 4 & Phase 10)

The Requirement: Emphasize that security_opt: - label:disable is not optional for the Mastercontainer.

Reason: Without this, even with correct host-side SELinux labels, the Mastercontainer is denied the groupadd and usermod syscalls required to grant the www-data user access to the GPU (/dev/dri/renderD128).

4. Handling Pitfall 13 (Phase 18)

Refinement: Update the instructions for the Immutable Guard.

Instruction: "Always apply chattr +i to the mount point while the drive is unmounted. If applied while mounted, it locks the physical drive instead of the OS folder, which will break Nextcloud’s ability to write data."

